Medical_sociology\" title=\"Medical sociology\">Medical</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Military_sociology\" title=\"Military sociology\">Military</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Organizational_theory\" title=\"Organizational theory\">Organizational</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Political_sociology\" title=\"Political sociology\">Political</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology_of_race_and_ethnic_relations\" title=\"Sociology of race and ethnic relations\">Race and ethnicity</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology_of_religion\" title=\"Sociology of religion\">Religion</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Rural_sociology\" title=\"Rural sociology\">Rural</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology_of_scientific_knowledge\" title=\"Sociology of scientific knowledge\">Science</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_change\" title=\"Social change\">Social change</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_movement\" title=\"Social movement\">Social movements</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_psychology_(sociology)\" title=\"Social psychology (sociology)\">Social psychology</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_stratification\" title=\"Social stratification\">Stratification</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_construction_of_technology\" title=\"Social construction of technology\">Technology</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Urban_sociology\" title=\"Urban sociology\">Urban</a></td></li></ul>\n</tr><tr><th class=\"navbox-abovebelow\" style=\"padding:0.1em\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Index_of_sociology_articles\" title=\"Index of sociology articles\">Browse</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding-top:0.2em;\">\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Sociology\" title=\"Portal:Sociology\">Portal</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/List_of_sociologists\" title=\"List of sociologists\">People</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/List_of_sociological_associations\" title=\"List of sociological associations\">Organizations</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/List_of_sociology_journals\" title=\"List of sociology journals\">Journals</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Index_of_sociology_articles\" title=\"Index of sociology articles\">Index</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Timeline_of_sociology\" title=\"Timeline of sociology\">Timeline</a></td></li></ul>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Sociology\" title=\"Template:Sociology\"><span title=\"View this template\">v</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Sociology\" title=\"Template talk:Sociology\"><span title=\"Discuss this template\">t</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Sociology&amp;action=edit\"><span title=\"Edit this template\">e</span></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></table>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content\" role=\"presentation\"><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><span class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>needs attention from an expert in Sociology</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please add a <i>reason</i> or a <i>talk</i> parameter to this template to explain the issue with the article. <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Sociology\" title=\"Wikipedia:WikiProject Sociology\">WikiProject Sociology</a> (or its <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Sociology\" title=\"Portal:Sociology\">Portal</a>) may be able to help recruit an expert.</span>  <small><i>(September 2009)</i></small><span class=\"hide-when-compact\"></span></span></td></tr></table>\n<p>The <b>sociology of immigration</b> involves the sociological analysis of immigration, particularly with respect to <a href=\"/wiki/Race_(classification_of_human_beings)\" title=\"Race (classification of human beings)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">race</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnicity\" title=\"Ethnicity\" class=\"mw-redirect\">ethnicity</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Social_structure\" title=\"Social structure\">social structure</a>, and political <a href=\"/wiki/Policy\" title=\"Policy\">policy</a>. Important concepts include <a href=\"/wiki/Cultural_assimilation\" title=\"Cultural assimilation\">assimilation</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Enculturation\" title=\"Enculturation\">enculturation</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Marginalization\" title=\"Marginalization\" class=\"mw-redirect\">marginalization</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Multiculturalism\" title=\"Multiculturalism\">multiculturalism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Postcolonialism\" title=\"Postcolonialism\">postcolonialism</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Transnationalism\" title=\"Transnationalism\">transnationalism</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Social_cohesion\" title=\"Social cohesion\" class=\"mw-redirect\">social cohesion</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div id=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Transnationalism\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Transnationalism</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Transnationalism\">Transnationalism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sociology_of_immigration&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Transnationalism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A more contemporary sociological analysis of immigration can be explored within the concept of <a href=\"/wiki/Transnationalism\" title=\"Transnationalism\">transnationalism</a>. This analysis is perhaps more concerned with the relational dimensions of immigration, particularly in terms of the ways in which families and relationships are maintained when members migrate to another country. Theorist Zlatko Skrbis argues that within a transnational network of families, the patterns of migration are intertwined with notions of 'emotion' and 'belonging'<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sociology_of_immigration&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology_of_race_and_ethnic_relations\" title=\"Sociology of race and ethnic relations\">Sociology of race and ethnic relations</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Race_(classification_of_human_beings)\" title=\"Race (classification of human beings)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Race (classification of human beings)</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnicity\" title=\"Ethnicity\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Ethnicity</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Black_feminism\" title=\"Black feminism\">Black feminism</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sociology_of_immigration&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation journal\">Skrbis, Z. \"Transnational Families: Theorizing Migration Emotions and Belonging\". <i>Journal of Intercultural Studies</i> <b>29</b> (3): 231\u2013246. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//dx.doi.org/10.1080%2F07256860802169188\">10.1080/07256860802169188</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASociology+of+immigration&amp;rft.atitle=Transnational+Families%3A+Theorizing+Migration+Emotions+and+Belonging&amp;rft.aufirst=Z&amp;rft.aulast=Skrbis&amp;rft.au=Skrbis%2C+Z&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1080%2F07256860802169188&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Intercultural+Studies&amp;rft.pages=231-246&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sociology_of_immigration&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cmd.princeton.edu\">Princeton Migration and Development Center</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gse.harvard.edu/hfrp/about.html\">Harvard Family Research Project</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"externa